<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">376. Healey, Deryck. Living with Color: The Handbook of Managing Colors in Your Home. New York: Rand-McNally, 1982. 167 pp. Bibl., glossary, color illus. ISBN 0-528-81549-0. </p><p class="annot">This British overview of color in interiors provides examples of color usage from around the world. The author discusses color theory and shows how color and other design elements have been used to create many beautiful interiors. Unique to this handsome book are photographs of rooms created by contemporary designers and architects inspired by color usage from the past and by other cultures. </p></div>
